<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,284,806,832]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves unknown, expanded submerged or floating leaves narrowly elliptic, 2.3–5.6 × 1.7–2.9, petiole 1.3–3.5, venation usually simple, 3–5 veins, the tertiary veins sometimes anastomosing, the apical leaves forming a floating rosette, leaves of terrestrial plants unknown. Flowers solitarY. Bracts persistent, 
<specimenCount box="[532,553,915,941]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[561,697,914,941]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<specimenCount box="[768,789,915,941]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[797,884,914,941]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long. StYles erect, &lt;
<quantity box="[1124,1211,914,941]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
long. Filament, erect &lt;
<quantity box="[160,247,950,977]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
long; anther 0.2–0.3 × 
<quantity box="[515,654,950,977]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 mm</quantity>
; pollen Yellow. Fruit not strumose, subsessile or on pedicel to 
<quantity box="[1365,1452,950,977]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
long, wider than or occasionally as wide as high, pale brown or rich brown contrasting with paler wing when mature, 0.8–1.3 × 
<quantity box="[250,387,1022,1049]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.4 mm</quantity>
, wing 
<quantity box="[461,547,1022,1049]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide all around, very even width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" box="[189,926,1058,1085]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,1058,1084]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Illustrations:</emphasis>
—plate 1174(18c–m) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fassett, N. C." box="[620,783,1058,1085]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[794,885,1058,1084]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1366,1388]" captionTargetBox="[347,1230,205,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[337,1251,187,1339]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fruits of South American Callitriche: a—C. albomarginata, b—C. antarctica, c—C. berteroana, d—C. ciliata, e—C. ciliata showing fibrils, f—C. concinna, g—C. dacryoidea, h—C. deflexa, i—C. ecarinata, j—C. hegelmaieriana, k—C. heterophylla, l—C. heteropoda." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424746/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,1094,1120]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[373,625,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="berteroana">
<emphasis box="[373,625,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche berteroana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[789,904,1094,1120]" country="Chile" name="Araucania" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Araucanía</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[959,1077,1094,1120]" country="Chile" name="Valparaiso" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Valparaíso</collectingRegion>
Provinces in 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1295,1094,1120]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Chile</collectingCountry>
, with a single record from the Juan Fernández Islands. Known altitudinal range: 
<quantity box="[879,967,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
. See map on page 
<quantity box="[1176,1247,1130,1156]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9022" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="in" value="193.0">193 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Fassett, N. C." box="[1254,1417,1130,1157]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1166,1192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Notes:</emphasis>
—The earliest appearance of this entity was in 
<bibRefCitation author="von Steudel, E. G." box="[798,1016,1166,1193]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" refId="ref31432" refString="von Steudel, E. G. (1840) Nomenclator botanicus, 2 nd ed., vol. 1. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart and Tubingen, 852 pp." type="book" year="1840">von Steudel (1840)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Steudel" authorityYear="1840" box="[1059,1333,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="berteroniana">
<emphasis box="[1059,1333,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche berteroniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, this name was not validly published because it lacked a diagnosis and a description (Arts. 38.1 and 38.3 of the 
<emphasis box="[1376,1435,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Code</emphasis>
). Von Steudel did, however, provide information on a gathering (“ 
<collectingCountry box="[884,945,1238,1264]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Chili</collectingCountry>
” and “ 
<emphasis box="[1029,1085,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Bert.</emphasis>
hrb. nr. 141”), which was later the basis for the first validly published name for this entity: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1867" box="[843,1180,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marginata" variety="berteroana">
<emphasis box="[843,995,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. marginata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1057,1180,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">berteroana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hegelmaier, C. F." box="[1236,1451,1274,1301]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref29459" refString="Hegelmaier, C. F. (1867) Zur Systematik von Callitriche. Verhandlungen des botanischen Vereins fur die Provinz Brandenburg und die angrenzenden Lander 9: 1 - 41, 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1867">Hegelmaier (1867)</bibRefCitation>
who provided the following information on the type: “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Bert." authorityName="Bert." box="[756,978,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnalis">
<emphasis box="[756,914,1310,1337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. autumnalis</emphasis>
Bert.
</taxonomicName>
in sched. 
<emphasis box="[1095,1263,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. Berteroiana</emphasis>
Steud. Herb. (et Nomencl.)” and “ 
<emphasis box="[336,350,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">β</emphasis>
kommt in 
<collectingCountry box="[474,535,1346,1372]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Chile</collectingCountry>
vor („in spongiosis humidis mont. La Leona 1828, Oct. fl. et fr.” Herb. Steud.)”. Hegelmaier therefore made an unequivocal reference to von Steudel’s name. The 
<typeStatus box="[1058,1156,1382,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">holotype</typeStatus>
was located at P (barcode P00697226). We should remark that 
<bibRefCitation author="Fassett, N. C." box="[544,759,1418,1445]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951: 192)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this entity to the infraspecific sphere of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hegelm.) Fassett (1951: 191 - 194" authorityName="Fassett" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Hegelm." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lechleri">
<emphasis box="[1334,1452,1418,1445]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. lechleri</emphasis>
(Hegelm.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Fassett, N. C." box="[256,521,1454,1481]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951: 191–194</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, t. 1174[18]), and listed isotypes (“ 
<emphasis box="[908,1041,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Bertero 141</emphasis>
(ISOTYPE of 
<emphasis box="[1180,1346,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. Berteroiana</emphasis>
Steud.— GH, MO)”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName box="[189,444,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="berteroana">
<emphasis box="[189,444,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche berteroana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[708,921,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[708,829,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in South America by its combination of fruit which are broader than long and broadlY winged throughout, some fruit on all specimens with pedicels &lt;
<quantity box="[1303,1389,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
long, combined with the presence of stem and leaf scales. It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Torrey (1856: 135)" authorityName="Torrey" authorityPageNumber="135" authorityYear="1856" box="[1015,1385,1598,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis box="[1015,1164,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. marginata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Torrey, J." box="[1170,1385,1598,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="61 - 184" refId="ref31615" refString="Torrey, J. (1856) Description of the general botanical collections. In: United States War Department (Org.) Explorations and surveys for a railroad route from the Mississippi River to the Pacific Ocean, part 5, No. 4. United States War Department, Washington, pp. 61 - 184, 25 plates. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11139" type="book chapter" year="1856">Torrey (1856: 135)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the fruit which are longer, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fassett" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Hegelm." box="[713,833,1634,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lechleri">
<emphasis box="[713,833,1634,1661]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. lechleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the consistently broader wing on the fruit and from both in the capacity to develop longer pedicels. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Warb. &amp; Eig) Lansdown et al. (2017 a: 92)" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityPageNumber="92" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Warb. &amp; Eig" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brutia" variety="naftolskyi">
<emphasis box="[868,968,1670,1697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. brutia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1024,1133,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">naftolskyi</emphasis>
(Warb. &amp; Eig) 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Bazos, I. &amp; Caria, M. C. &amp; Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J." pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref30075" refString="Lansdown, R. V., Bazos, I., Caria, M. C., Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J. (2017 a) New distribution and taxonomic information on Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) in the Mediterranean region. Phytotaxa 313 (1): 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 313.1.6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lansdown 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">et al</emphasis>
. (2017a: 92)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the broader wing of the fruit and yellow pollen. These differences are sufficient to justify its treatment as a separate species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
